{
  "uid": 1,
  "caption": "Network Activity",
  "description": "<p>One class for application-layer network traffic (v2.0).</p><p><b>Flow vs protocol.</b> <code>activity_id</code> is only for connection or flow lifecycle (open, close, traffic, reset, refuse, etc.). Things like HTTP methods, DNS query vs response, or DHCP message types belong in the protocol profile fields—not in <code>activity_id</code>.</p><p><b>How to tag the protocol.</b> Set <code>network_application_protocol_id</code> (and <code>app_protocol_name</code> when helpful). List active profiles in <code>metadata.profiles</code> (for example <code>network_http</code>, <code>network_dns</code>). If there is no profile yet, use <code>protocol_context</code>.</p><p><b>HTTP.</b> When HTTP applies (<code>network_application_protocol_id</code> = 1 or <code>network_http</code> in profiles), include at least one of <code>http_request</code> or <code>http_response</code>. This expectation is documented here in prose (not as a machine constraint in this repository).</p><p>Replaces: <code>http_activity</code>, <code>dns_activity</code>, <code>dhcp_activity</code>, <code>ftp_activity</code>, <code>smb_activity</code>, <code>ssh_activity</code>, <code>ntp_activity</code>, <code>rdp_activity</code>, <code>tunnel_activity</code>.</p><details class='ocsf-desc-details'><summary><b>Diagram: flow vs profiles</b> (click to expand)</summary><p style='margin-top:0.5rem'>Use <code>activity_id</code> for the connection or flow phase. Use <code>network_application_protocol_id</code> plus <code>metadata.profiles</code> to pick the profile, then populate that profile’s attributes for L7 semantics.</p><svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 580 262' role='img' aria-labelledby='na-prof-flow-title'><title id='na-prof-flow-title'>Mapping network_activity to protocol profiles</title><desc>Vertical flow: event class, activity_id for flow lifecycle, protocol id and profiles, then branches for HTTP, DNS, or protocol_context.</desc><defs><marker id='na-prof-arr' markerWidth='7' markerHeight='7' refX='6' refY='3.5' orient='auto'><polygon points='0 0, 7 3.5, 0 7' fill='#495057'/></marker></defs><rect x='50' y='8' width='480' height='36' rx='4' fill='#f8f9fa' stroke='#6c757d'/><text x='290' y='30' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='13' font-weight='600' fill='#212529'>network_activity</text><line x1='290' y1='44' x2='290' y2='52' stroke='#495057' stroke-width='1.5' marker-end='url(#na-prof-arr)'/><rect x='50' y='52' width='480' height='40' rx='4' fill='#fff' stroke='#6c757d'/><text x='290' y='72' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='12' fill='#212529'>activity_id → flow lifecycle (open, traffic, close, …)</text><text x='290' y='86' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='11' fill='#6c757d'>not HTTP method, DNS query/response, DHCP type, …</text><line x1='290' y1='92' x2='290' y2='100' stroke='#495057' stroke-width='1.5' marker-end='url(#na-prof-arr)'/><rect x='50' y='100' width='480' height='44' rx='4' fill='#e7f1ff' stroke='#0d6efd'/><text x='290' y='120' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='12' fill='#212529'>network_application_protocol_id + metadata.profiles</text><text x='290' y='136' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='11' fill='#495057'>e.g. network_http, network_dns, network_dhcp …</text><line x1='290' y1='144' x2='290' y2='152' stroke='#495057' stroke-width='1.5'/><line x1='115' y1='152' x2='455' y2='152' stroke='#495057' stroke-width='1.5'/><line x1='115' y1='152' x2='115' y2='160' stroke='#495057' stroke-width='1.5' marker-end='url(#na-prof-arr)'/><line x1='290' y1='152' x2='290' y2='160' stroke='#495057' stroke-width='1.5' marker-end='url(#na-prof-arr)'/><line x1='455' y1='152' x2='455' y2='160' stroke='#495057' stroke-width='1.5' marker-end='url(#na-prof-arr)'/><rect x='40' y='160' width='150' height='92' rx='4' fill='#fff' stroke='#6c757d'/><text x='115' y='182' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='11' font-weight='600' fill='#212529'>HTTP (id 1)</text><text x='115' y='198' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='11' fill='#495057'>profile: network_http</text><text x='115' y='216' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='10' fill='#495057'>http_request /</text><text x='115' y='230' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='10' fill='#495057'>http_response</text><rect x='215' y='160' width='150' height='92' rx='4' fill='#fff' stroke='#6c757d'/><text x='290' y='182' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='11' font-weight='600' fill='#212529'>DNS (id 2)</text><text x='290' y='198' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='11' fill='#495057'>profile: network_dns</text><text x='290' y='216' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='10' fill='#495057'>query, dns_operation_id,</text><text x='290' y='230' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='10' fill='#495057'>answers, rcode, …</text><rect x='390' y='160' width='150' height='92' rx='4' fill='#fff' stroke='#6c757d'/><text x='465' y='182' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='11' font-weight='600' fill='#212529'>No profile yet</text><text x='465' y='202' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='11' fill='#495057'>protocol_context</text><text x='465' y='222' text-anchor='middle' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-size='10' fill='#6c757d'>(structured JSON)</text></svg></details>",
  "extends": "network",
  "name": "network_activity",
  "associations": {
    "src_endpoint": [
      "user"
    ],
    "user": [
      "src_endpoint"
    ]
  },
  "attributes": {
    "$include": [
      "profiles/network_http.json",
      "profiles/network_dns.json",
      "profiles/network_dhcp.json",
      "profiles/network_ftp.json",
      "profiles/network_smb.json",
      "profiles/network_ssh.json",
      "profiles/network_ntp.json",
      "profiles/network_rdp.json",
      "profiles/network_tunnel.json"
    ],
    "activity_id": {
      "description": "Connection or flow lifecycle only. Do not encode HTTP methods, DHCP message types, or other L7 verbs here—use the protocol profile fields (e.g. <code>http_method_id</code>, <code>dhcp_message_type_id</code>).",
      "enum": {
        "1": {
          "caption": "Open",
          "description": "A new network connection was opened."
        },
        "2": {
          "caption": "Close",
          "description": "The network connection was closed."
        },
        "3": {
          "caption": "Reset",
          "description": "The network connection was abnormally terminated or closed by a middle device like firewalls."
        },
        "4": {
          "caption": "Fail",
          "description": "The network connection failed. For example a connection timeout or no route to host."
        },
        "5": {
          "caption": "Refuse",
          "description": "The network connection was refused. For example an attempt to connect to a server port which is not open."
        },
        "6": {
          "caption": "Traffic",
          "description": "Network traffic report for an established or connectionless flow."
        },
        "7": {
          "caption": "Listen",
          "description": "A network endpoint began listening for new network connections."
        }
      }
    },
    "dst_endpoint": {
      "description": "The responder of the network connection. In some contexts an event source cannot correctly identify the responder. Refer to <code>is_src_dst_assignment_known</code> for certainty."
    },
    "is_src_dst_assignment_known": {
      "group": "primary",
      "requirement": "recommended"
    },
    "network_application_protocol": {
      "group": "context",
      "requirement": "optional"
    },
    "network_application_protocol_id": {
      "description": "Normalized L7 protocol for this observation. Drives which optional profile attributes are populated.",
      "group": "context",
      "requirement": "recommended"
    },
    "dns_operation": {
      "group": "context",
      "requirement": "optional"
    },
    "http_method": {
      "group": "context",
      "requirement": "optional"
    },
    "dhcp_message_type": {
      "group": "context",
      "requirement": "optional"
    },
    "ftp_transfer_operation": {
      "group": "context",
      "requirement": "optional"
    },
    "smb_file_operation": {
      "group": "context",
      "requirement": "optional"
    },
    "ntp_association_mode": {
      "group": "context",
      "requirement": "optional"
    },
    "rdp_connection_phase": {
      "group": "context",
      "requirement": "optional"
    },
    "tunnel_session_event": {
      "group": "context",
      "requirement": "optional"
    },
    "protocol_context": {
      "description": "Extension point for protocols without a first-class profile.",
      "group": "context",
      "requirement": "optional"
    },
    "src_endpoint": {
      "description": "The initiator of the network connection. In some contexts an event source cannot correctly identify the initiator. Refer to <code>is_src_dst_assignment_known</code> for certainty."
    },
    "url": {
      "description": "The URL details relevant to the network traffic.",
      "group": "primary",
      "requirement": "recommended"
    }
  },
  "constraints": {
    "at_least_one": [
      "dst_endpoint",
      "src_endpoint"
    ]
  },
  "profiles": [
    "network_http",
    "network_dns",
    "network_dhcp",
    "network_ftp",
    "network_smb",
    "network_ssh",
    "network_ntp",
    "network_rdp",
    "network_tunnel"
  ],
  "references": [
    {
      "description": "D3FEND™ Ontology d3f:NetworkConnectionEvent",
      "url": "https://d3fend.mitre.org/event/d3f:NetworkConnectionEvent/"
    },
    {
      "description": "OCSF issue #1384 — Profiles for Network Activity",
      "url": "https://github.com/ocsf/ocsf-schema/issues/1384"
    }
  ]
}
